Reasoning: The paper deals with efficient projection of vectors onto the top principal components of a matrix, which is a problem in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of iterative algorithms and polynomial approximations, which are topics in numerical analysis and scientific computing, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SC (Scientific Computing) likely sub-categories as well. The problem of principal component projection also involves linear algebra and matrix computations, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
